{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nTwo work tickets (115b, 8c4f) burned close-gate cycles: their acceptance\ncriteria had \"done\" evidence that lives OUTSIDE the codebase (live-store fsck\nsurgery, phantom-dir deletion, changes landed through Gerrit) but were NOT tagged\n`[operator-attested]` (ADR-0043), so the completion verifier failed looking for\ncode proof until the tag was added retroactively. A cheap DETERMINISTIC pass-1\nlint that surfaces this at PLAN time — before claim — removes the whole\nround-trip. Rule-based lexicon checks are the proven high-recall/cheap tier for\nrequirement-defect shape (AQUSA-grade prior art); this project already ships two\nsuch lexicon lints in the same P6/P7 family (`p6_ac_quality`'s vague-term +\nverify-command lint at `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py:686`, and\n`p7_destructive` at `:762`), so this is a well-precedented extension, not a new\nmechanism.\n\n## What\n\nAdd an ADVISORY, prompt-less DETERMINISTIC lint (ADR-0016 `exec: DET`, the P6/AC\nfamily) that flags AC checklist items whose text carries operational-evidence\nmarkers (deploy / prod / live-run / IaC-apply / cloud-state / merge-gate /\nhuman-action / drill / store-surgery / recorded-attestation) but which are NOT\ntagged `[operator-attested]`. It NEVER blocks (advisory coaching only).\n\n### Design decisions (grounded against the code)\n\n- **It EXTENDS `p6_ac_quality`; it does NOT add a `P10` and does NOT touch\n  `criteria_routing.json`.** The static DET floor (`DET_CHECKS`,\n  `det_floor.py:880`) is hardcoded P1–P9 and enumerated in\n  `registry.py:78 CANONICAL_DET`; DET checks are NOT routed through\n  `criteria_routing.json`. `registry.validate_packaged_routing()`\n  (`registry.py:445-446`) flags any routing key not in `CANONICAL_LLM` as an\n  ORPHAN and fails CI, so a packaged DET routing entry is impossible without a\n  larger, out-of-scope change. And `.rebar/`-overlay `exec:DET` criteria run\n  through `det_invariants.run_project_det_checks` (`det_invariants.py:207`),\n  which scans CODE with a grounding detector (`engine_b`) — structurally wrong\n  for an AC-TEXT lexicon. The existing regression test\n  `tests/unit/test_det_invariants.py:327` already pins \"the lint EXTENDS p6 …\n  DET_CHECKS stays exactly P1-P9\", exactly matching how the verify-command lint\n  (G-3a) was folded into p6. So the correct home is `p6_ac_quality`, keeping\n  `DET_CHECKS` at 9 and `CANONICAL_DET` unchanged. The task's suggestion of a\n  `criteria_routing.json` entry is refuted by the code and is deliberately NOT\n  done; `p6_ac_quality` already ships in the packaged registry (no config flag),\n  satisfying \"advisory in packaged registry\".\n\n- **Single-source the tag matcher.** The canonical `[operator-attested]` matcher\n  is `workflow_ops._OPERATOR_ATTESTED_AC_RE` (`workflow_ops.py:61`), consumed by\n  the completion-verifier enrichment path (`workflow_ops.py:80\n  enrich_operator_attested`, `passes.py:769`). `det_floor` imports nothing from\n  `workflow_ops`, and `workflow_ops` imports `det_floor` lazily\n  (`workflow_ops.py:135`), so `det_floor` will OWN the regex as\n  `_OPERATOR_ATTESTED_TAG_RE` and `workflow_ops` will import it — no import cycle,\n  one source of truth, so the lint and the verifier agree on \"tagged\" by\n  construction (guarded by a unit test).\n\n- **Precision-first (advisory posture).** An advisory lint must not nag, so the\n  lexicon is tuned for precision with a codebase-verifiable SUPPRESSION co-signal\n  (drop items that name an in-repo proving command / test / doc / config-file\n  deliverable, or carry a \"… — landed on main\" trailer) and a NEGATION guard\n  (\"no live\", \"read-only provisioning\"). Recall is a reported figure, not a gate.\n\n### Self-gate (DETERMINISTIC — no LLM anywhere)\n\nRun the locked lexicon over the frozen historical AC corpus committed under\n`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/`. The corpus is the AC checklist items\nof the 556 E1 outcome-corpus tickets that resolve in the store\n(`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl` → 3091 AC items,\n31 already tagged `[operator-attested]`). Ground-truth for precision is a frozen\nper-item TP/FP adjudication of the full flagged set (a census ≥ the required\n50-item sample); recall is measured against the 31 tagged items with their tag\nstripped. Measured on this corpus: flag rate 2.07% (≤5%), recall 61% (19/31),\nprecision ~92% (census of 64 flagged items, 6 adjudicated false-positive), and\nboth known cases (115b, 8c4f) fire. NO LLM call runs in the eval or the lint.\n\n### Landing order (pre-registration, git-ancestry)\n\nLanded as a 2-commit Gerrit stack so the eval is committed BEFORE the lint is\nactive: commit 1 adds the frozen corpus + the harness + the committed `eval.json`\nresult and the detector helper `_operator_evidence_ac_gaps()` in `det_floor.py`\nin DORMANT form (defined, used only by the harness, not yet called by\n`p6_ac_quality`); commit 2 wires the helper into `p6_ac_quality` (activation),\nadds the unit tests + the `workflow_ops` single-source import, and documents the\nlint in `docs/plan-review-gate.md`.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py` — the `_OPERATOR_ATTESTED_TAG_RE`,\n  the operational-evidence lexicon (marker families + suppression + negation),\n  the pure helper `_operator_evidence_ac_gaps(text) -> list[(ac_line, markers)]`,\n  and its wiring into `p6_ac_quality` (append one advisory coaching issue per\n  gap; never changes P6's non-blocking status).\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py` — import\n  `_OPERATOR_ATTESTED_TAG_RE` from `det_floor` (drop the local duplicate).\n- `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/operator_attested_eval.py` — the\n  deterministic eval harness (imports the shipped helper; runs over the frozen\n  corpus; computes flag rate / recall / known-case firing; loads frozen precision\n  adjudications; asserts the gate).\n- `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/operator_attested_ac_corpus.jsonl` —\n  the frozen AC corpus.\n- `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/operator_attested_eval.json` — the\n  committed eval result (precision/recall/flag-rate/known-cases + adjudications +\n  PASS verdict).\n- `tests/unit/test_det_floor_operator_attested.py` — table-driven unit tests over\n  labeled AC strings (115b/8c4f fixtures fire; negative controls do not;\n  already-tagged items do not; agreement with `workflow_ops`).\n- `docs/plan-review-gate.md` — document the lint (advisory P6-family DET,\n  ADR-0016/0043).\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Any `criteria_routing.json` change (refuted by the code, see above).\n- A new `P10` DET check or any change to `CANONICAL_DET` / `DET_CHECKS`\n  cardinality.\n- Blocking posture, LLM rubric, or an `.rebar/` overlay entry.\n- Any human-adjudicated gold set (parked as idea e59d).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The deterministic lexicon eval is committed under\n  `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/operator_attested_eval.json` BEFORE the\n  lint is activated (its commit is a git ancestor of the p6 activation commit),\n  recording sampled precision ≥ 70% over a ≥ 50-item flagged sample AND overall\n  flag rate ≤ 5% over the frozen corpus, plus the recall figure. Proof:\n  `python -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/operator_attested_eval.json')); assert d['precision']['precision_pct']>=70 and d['precision']['sample_size']>=50 and d['flag_rate_pct']<=5.0 and d['gate']['verdict']=='PASS', d\"`\n  and `git merge-base --is-ancestor <eval-commit> <activation-commit>` exits 0.\n  (If the eval had failed the thresholds, the story closes deferred with the\n  failing result recorded instead.)\n- [ ] Both known cases fire on their historical (tag-stripped) AC text, pinned as\n  unit-test fixtures, and an already-tagged item does NOT fire. Proof:\n  `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_det_floor_operator_attested.py -q` passes,\n  including `test_known_case_115b_fires`, `test_known_case_8c4f_fires`, and\n  `test_tagged_item_not_flagged`.\n- [ ] The lint ships ADVISORY and prompt-less in the packaged floor: it extends\n  `p6_ac_quality` (which never blocks), `DET_CHECKS` stays exactly 9 and\n  `CANONICAL_DET` is unchanged, and no `criteria_routing.json` entry is added.\n  Proof: `python -c \"from rebar.llm.plan_review.det_floor import DET_CHECKS; assert len(DET_CHECKS)==9\"`;\n  `python -c \"from rebar.llm.plan_review import registry,det_floor; assert list(registry.CANONICAL_DET)==['P1','P2','P3','P4','P5','P6','P7','P8','P9']; assert registry.validate_packaged_routing()==[]\"`;\n  and a unit test asserting a `p6_ac_quality` result on an untagged operational\n  AC has `status=='fail'` with `blocking is False`.\n- [ ] The lint and the completion-verifier agree on \"tagged\": `det_floor` owns\n  `_OPERATOR_ATTESTED_TAG_RE` and `workflow_ops` imports it. Proof:\n  `python -c \"from rebar.llm.plan_review.det_floor import _OPERATOR_ATTESTED_TAG_RE as a; from rebar.llm.plan_review.workflow_ops import _OPERATOR_ATTESTED_AC_RE as b; assert a is b\"`\n  and a unit test asserting `_operator_evidence_ac_gaps` never flags a line that\n  `workflow_ops.operator_attested_ac_texts` recognizes as tagged.\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` documents the new advisory P6-family DET lint\n  (what it flags, that it is advisory/prompt-less, its self-gate result). Proof:\n  `grep -qi \"operator-attested\" docs/plan-review-gate.md`.\n- [ ] The whole suite stays green: `make lint && make typecheck && make test`\n  pass (or the targeted `det_floor` / `plan_review` / `criteria_overlay` subsets\n  plus the module-size gate).\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The change is landed on `main` through Gerrit\n  (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1, no unresolved comments), attested on this\n  ticket with the Gerrit change number(s) and the merge commit sha."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784344453904747001,"uuid":"4389feb7-4e89-4031-9b9f-49838d88c81a"}